types.section:
{{fr-noun|m}}

# {{lb|fr|French nuclear policy}} the [[recourse]] to the use of limited, [[substrategic|sub-]] or [[prestrategic]], [[tactical]] nuclear strikes as part of a [[nuclear deterrent]], constituting a “final warning” and the last measure before strategic nuclear [[bombardment]]; {{n-g|also}}, such a strike
#* '''1988''', David Garnham, ''The Politics of European Defense Cooperation'', pages [http://books.google.co.uk/books?ei=NApMT8bAG8Lg8APW6cCPDg&id=2cYdAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&q=%22ultime+avertissement+%28final+warning%29%22#search_anchor 53] and [http://books.google.co.uk/books?ei=NApMT8bAG8Lg8APW6cCPDg&id=2cYdAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&q=%22ultime+avertissement+weapons%22#search_anchor 56]:
#*: {{quote|fr|They were not battlefield weapons but the '''''l’ultime avertissement''''' (final warning) prior to the use of strategic forces.<br/>{{...}}<br/>French conventional forces have two roles: to defend the FRG conventionally alongside the allies ''if the president makes that determination'', but also to conduct the national deterrent maneuver (to test the enemy’s intentions) prior to the use of prestrategic ('''''l’ultime avertissement''''') weapons.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1989|title=A Rand Note|section=MMCML-MMCMLVIII, pages [http://books.google.co.uk/books?ei=NApMT8bAG8Lg8APW6cCPDg&id=KZooAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&q=%22his+ultime+avertissement%22#search_anchor page 26]
|passage=It is clear{{...}}that the new tactical nuclear arsenal will be considerably more diversified, flexible, survivable, and capable of a larger range of military missions, thus presenting the French President with greater choice in executing his “'''''ultime avertissement'''''.”}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1991|author=Diego A. Ruiz Palmer|title=French Strategic Options in the 1990s|page=53|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=38kgAQAAIAAJ&q=%22ultime+avertissement%22&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=OBFMT5OAOYit8QP32Iy5Dg&redir_esc=y|passage=Soviet uncertainty in such circumstances would be contrary to the implied escalation-control intent of the '''''ultime avertissement''''' strike.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1996|author=Bruce D. Larkin|title=Nuclear Designs|page=38|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=pHIpdyMhSZkC&pg=PA38&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oRtMT7T_C8Kv8QO8o9XBDg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22ultime%20avertissement%22&f=false|passage=The French doctrine of “'''''ultime avertissement'''''” — employing “substrategic” systems as a last warning.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=2007|author=Laura Neack|title=Elusive Security|page=107|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=0IGS8uS16a4C&pg=PA107&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-R5MT8eHMdG78gP1_KSTDg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22ultime%20avertissement%22&f=false|passage=French policy also included the idea of a “final warning,” or '''''ultime avertissement'''''.}}
#* '''2009''', Marco Rimanelli, ''The A to Z of NATO and Other International Security Organizations'', “[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=TLaUACsJpYcC&pg=PA272&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-R5MT8eHMdG78gP1_KSTDg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22ultime%20avertissement%22&f=false ''force de frappe'']”
#*: {{quote|fr|France’s nuclear weapons would be a “warning shot” ('''''ultime avertissement''''') against enemy advances prior to a full-scale nuclear attack on key Soviet cities, in a “worse-case” ''stratégie du faible au fort'' (“weak-to-strong strategy”) of mutual assured destruction.}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=2011|author=Venance Journé|chapterurl=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vqP2wLjKxYgC&pg=PT212&dq=%22ultime+avertissement%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-R5MT8eHMdG78gP1_KSTDg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22ultime%20avertissement%22&f=false|chapter=France’s Nuclear Stance|title=Getting to Zero|editors=Catherine M. Kelleher; Judith Reppy
|passage=This credible use, consisting in the capacity to strike precisely with weapons of a lower yield, has a concept attached: the '''''ultime avertissement''''', now also called the ''avertissement nucléaire''.}}
#* {{seemoreCites|fr}}

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|tactical nuclear strike}} {{l|en|avertissement nucléaire}}

